00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:29,250
despite his expectations
for the final outcome.

4
00:00:29,333 --> 00:00:31,125
Before he can go forward,

5
00:00:31,208 --> 00:00:35,333
there is one more enemy
Lelouch must confront.

6
00:00:35,416 --> 00:00:38,125
However, this one is
different than all others.

7
00:00:38,208 --> 00:00:41,375
For this enemy is
human nature itself.

8
00:00:41,458 --> 00:00:44,708
Hope and atonement.
Freedom and solitude.

9
00:00:44,791 --> 00:00:48,708
That mass of matter and
energy known as the world...

10
00:00:48,791 --> 00:00:53,250
Keeps on flowing forward despite
the desires of any one man.

11
00:02:41,375 --> 00:02:45,541
[V.V.] Charles, have you learned
anything by becoming emperor?

12
00:02:45,625 --> 00:02:48,583
Yes, big brother.
All people are liars.

13
00:02:48,666 --> 00:02:52,333
And this vast nation we call
Britannia never changes.

14
00:02:52,416 --> 00:02:53,875
[V.V.]
That may be true,

15
00:02:53,958 --> 00:02:56,333
but it's just human
nature, isn't it?

16
00:02:56,416 --> 00:02:58,333
[EMPEROR]
Perhaps you're right about that.

17
00:02:58,416 --> 00:03:02,833
[V.V.] Charles you won't forget,
will you? Our contract?

18
00:03:02,916 --> 00:03:08,833
[EMPEROR] I know. To kill God
and smash this world of lies...

19
00:03:15,833 --> 00:03:17,000
[ROLO]
That was a close call,

20
00:03:17,083 --> 00:03:19,458
big brother. Shirley
regained her memory.

21
00:03:19,541 --> 00:03:22,458
She had a gun, and she
was coming after you.

22
00:03:22,541 --> 00:03:25,541
[LELOUCH] I see. So you were
the one who killed her.

23
00:03:25,625 --> 00:03:30,750
Yes, I did it for you; I have
to eliminate your enemies.

24
00:03:30,833 --> 00:03:32,000
[LELOUCH]
Rolo...

25
00:03:32,083 --> 00:03:33,625
[ROLO]
What, big brother?

26
00:03:36,041 --> 00:03:39,750
You handled it very well.
If it weren't for you,

27
00:03:39,833 --> 00:03:42,041
everybody would've known
about my secret.

28
00:03:42,125 --> 00:03:45,500
Exactly and it isn't just your
secret anymore, brother.

29
00:03:45,583 --> 00:03:49,541
[LELOUCH] True. So, shall we
destroy the Geass Order now?

30
00:03:49,625 --> 00:03:50,708
[ROLO]
Uh?!

31
00:03:50,791 --> 00:03:51,833
[LELOUCH]
The Black Knights can wipe out

32
00:03:51,916 --> 00:03:54,250
the source of Geass
once and for all.

33
00:03:54,333 --> 00:03:56,083
[ROLO]
Big brother, we can't.

34
00:03:56,166 --> 00:03:58,458
There are still
Geass users there.

35
00:03:58,541 --> 00:04:00,916
If we keep avoiding
this, we'll never win.

36
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:03,833
Remember, this is for our
happiness. For both of us.

37
00:04:03,916 --> 00:04:05,083
For both of us?

38
00:04:05,166 --> 00:04:09,000
That's right. V.V. has
begun to suspect you.

39
00:04:11,541 --> 00:04:13,625
[LELOUCH]
Are you afraid of V.V.?

40
00:04:13,708 --> 00:04:16,208
[ROLO] Well, he was
the one who found me.

41
00:04:16,291 --> 00:04:20,125
Still, Lelouch, can I
really believe in you?

42
00:04:20,208 --> 00:04:21,333
[LELOUCH]
Of course.

43
00:04:21,416 --> 00:04:23,708
We're the only brothers
we have, aren't we?

44
00:04:24,666 --> 00:04:26,291
[CORNELIA]
Are you going to kill me?

45
00:04:26,375 --> 00:04:31,083
Or control me with your Geass?
Like you did to Euphy?

46
00:04:31,166 --> 00:04:32,875
To prove your
sister's innocence,

47
00:04:32,958 --> 00:04:37,041
you renounced your position gave
up everything. That's inspiring.

48
00:04:37,125 --> 00:04:37,875
[CORNELIA grunts]

49
00:04:37,958 --> 00:04:39,583
You made me think, Cornelia.

50
00:04:39,666 --> 00:04:42,625
Is there any more splendid
relationship in this entire

51
00:04:42,708 --> 00:04:44,958
world than that of
loyal siblings?

52
00:04:46,833 --> 00:04:49,208
[DOCTOR] Organ failure
due to gunshot wounds

53
00:04:49,291 --> 00:04:50,750
and loss of blood.

54
00:04:50,833 --> 00:04:54,375
[SUZAKU] Shirley. You're
saying that she shot herself?

55
00:04:54,458 --> 00:04:56,375
[DOCTOR]
Yes. Apparently on impulse.

56
